sia generate a critical mass of evidence that indicates criminal intent on the part of the Nazi regime to destroy the Roma as a distinct group. Other chapters examine the failure of the West German State to deliver justice, the Romani collective memory of the genocide, and the current political and historical debates. As this revealing volume shows, however inconsistent or geographically limited, over time, the mass murder acquired a systematic character and came to include ever larger segments of the Romani population regardless of the social status of individual members of the community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aRomani Genocide, 1939-1945vCongresses. 0aRomanieszGermanyxHistoryy20th centuryvCongresses. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xAtrocitiesvCongresses. 7aHISTORY / Military / Biological & Chemical Warfare.2bisacsh1 aBlumer, Nadine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFogg, Shannon L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreund, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoller, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKapralski, Sławomir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKorb, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMargalit, Gilad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolonari, Vladimir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTyaglyy, Mikhail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeiss-Wendt, Anton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeiss-Wendt, Anton, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Com